# Wayfare — Project Rules

## Stack

- **Frontend**: Next.js 14 (`web/`), MapLibre, Zustand, Tailwind
- **Backend**: FastAPI async (`api/`), LangGraph concierge, SSE streaming
- **Data**: Postgres 16 + PostGIS + pgvector (single engine), Redis cache
- **Ingestion**: Re-runnable pipeline in `ingestion/` (`make seed`)
- **Cities**: Lisbon and Barcelona (Title-case in API/UI, lowercase in `CITIES` env)

## Repository Layout

```
api/           FastAPI routers, agents, repository (SQL lives here)
ingestion/     Load + enrich stages (schema, listings, embeddings, summaries)
web/           Next.js app (deploy root on Vercel)
docker/        db + backend Dockerfiles
schema.sql     Idempotent DDL (also applied by ingestion schema stage)
```

## Agent Principles

- **Minimal diffs** — fix the requested issue; do not refactor unrelated code
- **Match existing style** — naming, types, and patterns in surrounding files
- **No secrets in git** — never commit `.env`, `api/.env`, or `data/`; use `.env.example` templates
- **Tests** — add only when requested or when covering real behavior
- **Comments** — only for non-obvious business or SQL logic

## Deployment

- **Backend**: Render (Docker) — `travel-api`, private `travel-db`, Redis
- **Frontend**: Vercel — root directory `web`, env `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` (build-time)
- **DB seed**: `pg_dump -Fc` via `docker compose cp` (never PowerShell `>` redirect on binary dumps)
- **Render DB host**: use Internal Connect address (e.g. `travel-db-xxxx:5432`), not bare service name

## Live URLs

- Web: https://wayfare-ai-travel.vercel.app
- API: https://wayfare-ai-travel.onrender.com

